--- @target: PI
The mathematical constant Pi (3.14159...). Represents the ratio of a circle's circumference to its diameter.
---

--- @target: E
The mathematical constant E (2.71828...). The base of natural logarithms.
---

--- @target: TAU
The mathematical constant Tau (6.28318...). Equal to 2 * Pi.
---

--- @target: pi
Returns the mathematical constant Pi.
---

--- @target: e
Returns the mathematical constant E.
---

--- @target: tau
Returns the mathematical constant Tau.
---

--- @target: abs
Returns the absolute value of an integer.

@param value The integer to get the absolute value of.
@return The absolute value (always non-negative).
---

--- @target: min
Returns the smaller of two integers.

@param a First integer.
@param b Second integer.
@return The smaller value between a and b.
---

--- @target: max
Returns the larger of two integers.

@param a First integer.
@param b Second integer.
@return The larger value between a and b.
---

--- @target: clamp
Constrains a value to remain within a specified range.

@param value The value to clamp.
@param min The minimum bound (inclusive).
@param max The maximum bound (inclusive).
@return The clamped value within [min, max].
---

--- @target: pow
Computes base raised to the power of exponent.

@param base The base value.
@param exponent The exponent value.
@return base raised to exponent.
---

--- @target: sqrt
Computes the square root of a floating-point number.

@param value The value to square root.
@return The square root of value.
---

--- @target: floor
Rounds a floating-point number down to the nearest integer.

@param value The value to floor.
@return The largest integer less than or equal to value.
---

--- @target: ceil
Rounds a floating-point number up to the nearest integer.

@param value The value to ceil.
@return The smallest integer greater than or equal to value.
---

--- @target: round
Rounds a floating-point number to the nearest integer using "half away from zero" rounding.

@param value The value to round.
@return The nearest integer to value.
---

--- @target: trunc
Truncates a floating-point number toward zero.

@param value The value to truncate.
@return The integer part of value (fractional part removed).
---

--- @target: deg_to_rad
Converts an angle from degrees to radians.

@param x Angle in degrees.
@return Angle in radians.
---

--- @target: rad_to_deg
Converts an angle from radians to degrees.

@param x Angle in radians.
@return Angle in degrees.
---

--- @target: approx_equal
Checks if two floating-point numbers are approximately equal within a given epsilon.

@param a First number.
@param b Second number.
@param epsilon Maximum allowed difference.
@return True if equal within epsilon.
---

--- @target: sin
Computes the sine of an angle in radians.

@param value Angle in radians.
@return The sine of value.
---

--- @target: cos
Computes the cosine of an angle in radians.

@param value Angle in radians.
@return The cosine of value.
---

--- @target: tan
Computes the tangent of an angle in radians.

@param value Angle in radians.
@return The tangent of value.
---

--- @target: asin
Computes the arcsine (inverse sine) of a value.

@param value A value in the range [-1, 1].
@return The arcsine in radians.
---

--- @target: acos
Computes the arccosine (inverse cosine) of a value.

@param value A value in the range [-1, 1].
@return The arccosine in radians.
---

--- @target: atan
Computes the arctangent (inverse tangent) of a value.

@param value Any real number.
@return The arctangent in radians.
---

--- @target: atan2
Computes the four-quadrant arctangent of y and x.

@param y The y-coordinate.
@param x The x-coordinate.
@return The angle in radians between the positive x-axis and the point (x, y).
---

--- @target: ln
Computes the natural logarithm (base E).

@param value A positive number.
@return The natural logarithm of value.
---

--- @target: log_ten
Computes the base-10 logarithm.

@param value A positive number.
@return The base-10 logarithm of value.
---

--- @target: log2
Computes the base-2 logarithm.

@param value A positive number.
@return The base-2 logarithm of value.
---

--- @target: log
Computes the logarithm with a custom base.

@param value The value to compute the logarithm of.
@param base The base of the logarithm.
@return The logarithm of value in the specified base.
---

--- @target: exp
Computes E raised to the power of value (e^value).

@param value The exponent.
@return e raised to value.
---

--- @target: is_nan
Checks if a floating-point value is NaN (Not a Number).

@param value The value to check.
@return True if value is NaN.
---

--- @target: is_infinite
Checks if a floating-point value is positive or negative infinity.

@param value The value to check.
@return True if value is infinite.
---

--- @target: is_finite
Checks if a floating-point value is a finite number (not NaN and not infinite).

@param value The value to check.
@return True if value is finite.
---